PRIMARY PURPOSE OF JOB
The Information Security Analyst is responsible for the ongoing monitoring of information and cyber security procedures and protocols for the protection of the organizations’ computer networks and information. Performs a variety of tasks.
EXPECTATIONS OF ALL SOUTHERN BANK TEAM MEMBERS
Southern Bank team members are a family, rooted in the communities we serve and working together to be the best in our industry, utilizing innovative ideas and strong products. The Southern Bank Patch illustrates these ideals.
Ensures the confidentiality of customer non-public personal information and secures information systems to comply with bank regulations.
ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS AND PERFORMANCE AREAS
Assists in monitoring information security directives as mandated by GLBA, SOX, and FFIEC guidelines;
Monitors and reviews user activity for information security processes;
Performs vulnerability scanning and reporting;
Recommend security enhancements to management;
Assists the ISO in performing information security, cybersecurity, and IT asset risk assessments to ensure that information systems are adequately protected and meet guidelines;
Investigates and reports all information security violations and breaches;
Maintains a current understanding of the IT threat landscape for the industry;
Review and responds to tickets in the security board;
Monitors the SIEM;
Performs reporting to Manager as required; and,
All other duties as assigned.
The following specifications are general guidelines based on the minimum education and experience normally considered essential to the satisfactory performance of this position. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill and/or ability required to perform the position in a satisfactory manner. Individual abilities may result in some deviation from these guidelines.
KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, AND ABILITIES
Strong verbal and written communication skills;
Ability to work independently and effectively;
Knowledge of financial services regulations and guidance, such as GLBA, SOX, FFIEC;
Ability to implement security controls; and,
Broad understanding of security frameworks and concepts.
EDUCATION, TRAINING AND EXPERIENCE REQUIREMENTS
Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science or related field or equivalent related experience required; and,
At least 3-5 years of experience in computer systems.
CORE COMPETENCIES
Family & Trust: Southern Bank team members build relationships based on trust and mutual respect, maintain an inclusive and honest environment and uphold integrity and transparency in all interactions.
Rooted & Service: Southern Bank team members are committed to serving customers, communities and teams with purpose, professionalism, and respect, while effectively communicating and actively listening to meet their needs.
Innovation & Strength: Southern Bank team members foster collaboration and continuous improvement, encourage visionary thinking, and strive for excellence to drive the organization forward.
Information Monitoring: Setting up ongoing procedures to collect and review information needed to manage an organization or ongoing activities within it.
Initiating Action: Taking prompt action to accomplish objectives; Taking action to achieve goals beyond what is required; being proactive.
Continuous Learning: Actively identifying new areas for learning; regularly creating and taking advantage of learning opportunities; and using newly gained knowledge and skill on the job and learning through their application.

At Bayer we’re visionaries, driven to solve the world’s toughest challenges and striving for a world where 'Health for all Hunger for none’ is no longer a dream, but a real possibility. We’re doing it with energy, curiosity and sheer dedication, always learning from unique perspectives of those around us, expanding our thinking, growing our capabilities and redefining ‘impossible’. There are so many reasons to join us. If you’re hungry to build a varied and meaningful career in a community of brilliant and diverse minds to make a real difference, there’s only one choice.

Sr Identity Security Eng

As a Senior Identity Security Engineer at Bayer, you play a pivotal role in designing, implementing, and operating cybersecurity solutions for Bayer’s systems and products. Your expertise in Sailpoint Identity Security Cloud (IdentityNow) ensures compliance with Bayer’s security policies and standards. You collaborate with IT and business partners to embed security in hardware and software evaluation, selection, installation, and configuration processes. Your work maintains the operational efficiency, performance, and reliability of security systems, integrating them into IT service management and incident response processes. You analyze and recommend improvements to network, system, and application architectures, assisting in updating cybersecurity policies, architectures, and standards. You respond to audits, penetration tests, and vulnerability assessments, and design secure infrastructure solutions to prevent unauthorized access. Regular security assessments are conducted to identify vulnerabilities and potential risks, aligning with Cyber Security Architects to implement security architecture standards and best practices.
YOUR TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
Design, implement, and operate cybersecurity solutions specialized in Sailpoint Identity Security Cloud (IdentityNow);
Collaborate with IT and business partners to ensure security in hardware and software evaluation, selection, installation, and configuration;
Maintain operational efficiency, performance, and reliability of security systems, integrating into IT service management and incident response processes;
Analyze and recommend improvements to network, system, and application architectures;
Assist in reviewing and updating cybersecurity policies, architectures, and standards;
Respond to audits, penetration tests, and vulnerability assessments;
Design and implement secure infrastructure solutions, including network security, configuration management, storage security, and IAM;
Conduct regular security assessments to identify vulnerabilities and potential risks;
Align with Cyber Security Architects to implement security architecture standards and best practices.
WHO YOU ARE:
Bayer seeks an incumbent who possesses the following:
Required Qualifications:
BS or MA in computer science, cybersecurity, or a related field, though relevant working experience may be considered an equivalent;
Experience with scripting, software development, or web development using PowerShell or Python for automation;
ITIL knowledge in processes (Incident, Problem, Change & Request Management) and tools (ServiceNow) preferred;
Experience with Microsoft Azure, AWS, or GCP cloud services is advantageous;
Experience working in a regulated environment (e.g., GxP) is advantageous;
Experience with agile methodology such as SCRUM and/or tools such as Azure DevOps.
Preferred Qualifications:
7-10+ years of experience in a leading role within cybersecurity, with previous experience in a security engineering role highly desired;
At least 3 years of experience and ideally certified with IAM solutions specialized in Sailpoint Identity Security Cloud (IdentityNow), complemented by experience in Entra ID and CyberArk;
Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP) desired but not required;
Understanding of organizational mission, values, and goals and consistently applying this knowledge.

